Plateau State Governor, Simon Bako Lalong has granted absolute pardon to one Evaritus C. Mozie; a prisoner facing life imprisonment. Lalong stated this at his inaugural speech at the Rwang Pam stadium in Jos on Wednesday that the pardon is granted for reasons of good conduct and determination to continue to be productive with effect from the date of sentence. He said the pardon was in exercise of the powers conferred on him as governor in Section 212 of the amended 1999 Constitution of the Federal Republic Of Nigeria after due consultation with the State Advisory Council On Prerogative Of Mercy. “As a mark of our appreciation and thanksgiving to God for the guidance, protection and successes recorded, and in exercise of the powers conferred on me as Governor in Section 212 of the Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria 1999 (as amended), after due consultation with the State Advisory Council On Prerogative Of Mercy, I have granted Prerogative of Mercy to one prisoner, Mr. Evaristus C. Mozie from life imprisonment to absolute pardon,” he said. ...Lalong pardons 7 prisoners Lalong pardons 7 prisoners New Year: Lalong pardons 4 prisoners Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin